reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It rides nicely on my chest.
reviews.reviewText: The pouch is the perfect size and weight. It rides comfortably on my chest and allows easy, quick access to contents. Zippers are good quality and pockets are adequate. I've probably had ten different pouches over the years and this is by far the best.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I used this to carry my wallet, passport and change around Portugal. It worked great, was comfortable, held up, and matched my clothes well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Used this on an 8 week cross European trip this cross body bag was almost perfect. It has plenty of room with many pockets that I used for my iPods to Money to Passport. It fit well and the circular clip is nice as well.The only issue is with the main compartments divider. It’s a nylon fabric that really could use some rigidity. It was a teeny bit difficult to fish around it to get stuff or to store stuff.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars I really love idea small purse.
reviews.reviewText: I am very disappointed about quality of zippers and fabric finishing. I use only a couple of times and I have a problems with zipper. zipper got stuck a couple of times and fabrics start to falling apart close to zipper. I wish I can get new one and replace this one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This has been my daily carry fora few months now. It's held up quite well, and the size is perfect. Will buy again if this one breaks!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I thought this big so that I can have a few drinks and maybe something to snack on while biking, after finding out I could barely fit two small cans of soda inside it and after about a 20 minute bike ride the easy to detach strap was bent open and was constantly falling off my shoulder. Also this bag doesn't like to stay in place on your back or your chest matter if the strap is shortened or made longer it tends to slide to your side into an awkward position. I do not recommend anyone to buy this and as it stands I will probably donate this bag to Goodwill and hope someone has a better use for it, and get myself something that will actually be a halfway decent bag.
